reviews.text: It has grown so much since I was young..still beautiful. Lake Champlain . The only reason it was never listed as a great lake is because u can see the other side. But,it was big enough. I was born in VT. & spent many years on & off there. Lake Champlain is a place for BBQ'S, swimming & just  escaping. Having family & or friends fun.
We always love coming down here for a walk or just to play in the field with the kids. All year they have fun stuff going on usually, kids day, fourth of July with fireworks, tons of events.
The sun is shining, a breeze is blowing, and the lake is frozen over from shore to shore. It's an amazing day on the waterfront in Burlington!

This is a great place to watch the sunset. There are lots of show's during the summer,wide variety of shops, dispensary, ferry, awesome bike path, short ride to North Beach. There is a dog park, skatepark, lots of places to sit, wheelchair accessible and lots of grass to walk on, parking,boat ramps docks, playground.

Great spot on the Lake in downtown Burlington.  Convenient to parking, docks, a waterfront walking trail, Skinny Pancake crepe shop and the Leahy museum.  More than a bit cold in the winter but usually delightful in the summer and fall.  Short walk uphill to everything in downtown Burlington, a great spot to visit.

Everyone here was so extremly nice to me and they all were stop helpful! (I've never eaten Thai before) The food was great, the drink was great & the service was just awesome! I wish all places were as friendly as they were here!

Came in today. Waited 45 mins thinking the food is almost ready. When I go and ask the worker about the wait time for food, she says it will take another 10 mins. Canceled the order and left with no food. Who takes 50+ mins to cook during lunch hour. Plus it was only one person serving all the customers and it took some time before she came to take our order. If you know it's going to be busy, have more people to help during peak hours. This is unacceptable. I would not give a star but that's the only option available. I would not recommend this place.
